headline: Vanguard Will Now Allow Crypto ETFs on Its Platform
summary: Starting on Tuesday, Vanguard will allow ETFs and mutual funds that primarily hold select cryptocurrencies, including Bitcoin, Ether, XRP, and Solana, to be eligible for trading on its platform.  It’s a compromise that belies the firm’s long-standing view that digital assets are too volatile and speculative for serious portfolios and comes despite a more than $1 trillion drawdown in crypto market value since early October.

content.title: Vanguard Will Now Allow Crypto ETFs on Its Platform
content.summary: Starting on Tuesday, Vanguard will allow ETFs and mutual funds that primarily hold select cryptocurrencies, including Bitcoin, Ether, XRP, and Solana, to be eligible for trading on its platform.  It’s a compromise that belies the firm’s long-standing view that digital assets are too volatile and speculative for serious portfolios and comes despite a more than $1 trillion drawdown in crypto market value since early October.

headline: Fed chair candidates: What to know about Kevin Hassett
summary: There are five candidates being considered for the next Federal Reserve chair when Jerome Powell's term ends in May 2026, according to a shortlist kept by Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent. Kevin Hassett, the director of the National Economic Council under the Trump administration, is currently believed to be the frontrunner for President Trump's pick as Federal Reserve chair to replace Jerome Powell next year. Yahoo Finance Fed Correspondent Jennifer Schonberger outlines key information to know about Hassett. For more, check out Jennifer Schonberger's profiles of the other four shortlist candidates: former Fed Governor Kevin Warsh, current Fed Governor Chris Waller, Fed Vice Chair of Supervision Michelle Bowman, and BlackRock's (BLK) head of fixed income Rick Rieder. Make sure to also watch Jen's interview with Hassett and Yahoo Finance anchor Julie Hyman's interview with Rieder. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Catalysts.
